          About Blockchain
        </a>
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="blockchain_general">
      <div class="panel-body">
        <p>The blockchain are cryptographically linked and decentrally stored datasets. Each dataset contains a fingerprint (hash value) of the previous dataset, a time stamp and further transaction data. Because later sets build on previous sets and confirm them as correct, it is impossible to change or delete those earlier sets without changing all the data that builds on them. However, such a change is not possible due to the distributed storage of the data and would be recognized immediately.</p>
        <p>Sealing documents uses this guaranteed data integrity property of the blockchain.</p>
      </div>
